        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p>The band of this ring is made from blue-colored iron and has two sharp, decorative protrusions on each side of the red-stone inlay. It feels quite heavy and reliable. Wearing this ring grants you a +2 item bonus to Deception and Diplomacy checks, but only if the associated checks involve haggling or bargaining over a purchase or trade.</p>\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span style=\"font-family: 'Pathfinder2eActions'; font-size: 1.8em; display: inline;\">T</span> envision, interact</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You can determine if an item is magical simply by handling it. You detect no other indication of its power, only whether or not it is magical, granting the effects of a 1st-level @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Detect Magic]{Detect Magic} spell that affects only the object.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Automatically applied effects:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>+2 item bonus to Deception and Diplomacy checks to haggle or bargain</li>\n</ul>"
